FBIS3-23218 "jptot011__l94034" JPRS-TOT-94-011-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 10 March 1994 LATIN AMERICA MEXICO Chiapas Peasant Leader Killed, Bishop Threatened PA1003024394 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 0000 GMT 10 Mar 94 PA1003024394 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Live report by Mary Carmen Camacho in Tuxtla Gutierrez, Chiapas; from the "ACIR Radio News" newscast] [Text] Once again, there is a lot of tension in Chiapas. There have been many protests by people either in favor or against dialogues with the EZ [not further identified], which are being held at the San Cristobal de las Casas Cathedral. Bishop Samuel Ruiz has received death threats. There is a lot of activity in Chiapas State. Let us hear from Mary Carmen Camacho, who is in Tuxtla Gutierrez, the Chiapas State capital. Good evening, Mary Carmen. [Camacho] Good evening, Pepe. Here is my report. Today, eight masked men killed Mariano Perez Diaz, regional leader of the Emiliano Zapata Peasant Organization. Francisco Meneses Gazon, municipal president of Simojovel, reported that the peasant leader was killed this morning on the doorstep of his home in El Carmito, 15 km from Simojovel. The son of the [word indistinct] leader in northern Chiapas was wounded in the attack. [passage omitted on labor issues]
